summary:
I am a teacher trainer, curriculum designer, and language assessor.

Currently I am working at Teacher Education Department at Hogeschool Utrecht, specializing in Writing and coaching students with their internships. In my lessons, I give customized guidance to each student and use content related speaking and writing subjects, reading texts and TED talks.

My colleagues describe me as hardworking, well-organised, enthusiastic and friendly. I get on well with everyone in a team and I work efficiently even in chaotic circumstances. In my classes I enjoy getting to know my students and following their personal progress.

I have a BA in English Language Education, a master in Business Administration and a master in Fine Arts Education.

In my free time, I love reading books, watching series and taking a walk.
